HEADWORD: friendly fire
<hw>friend"ly fire`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Weapons
fire{9}, such as artillery or aerial bombardment, from one's own forces;
-- used mostly when troops do damage or cause casualties among their own
forces; <as>as, the tank was hit by <ex>friendly
fire</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
